Class InlineEditController

java.lang.Object
com.oracle.javafx.scenebuilder.kit.editor.util.InlineEditController
All Implemented Interfaces:
InlineEdit
@Component
@Scope("document")
@Lazy
public class InlineEditController
extends Object
implements InlineEdit
Controller used to in line edit nodes. The inline edit controller will display TextInputControl within a popup window.

    • textEditingSessionDidBegin

      public void textEditingSessionDidBegin​(javafx.util.Callback<Void,​Boolean> requestSessionEnd)
      Tells this editor that a text editing session has started. The editor controller may invoke the requestSessionEnd() callback if it needs the text editing session to stop. The callback should; - either stop the text editing session, invoke textEditingSessionDidEnd() and return true - either keep the text editing session on-going and return false
      Specified by:
      textEditingSessionDidBegin in interface InlineEdit
      Parameters:
      requestSessionEnd - Callback that should end the text editing session or return false
